<tbox>
    <!-- Class 81 (Clematis) -->
    [Class_81] sqsubseteq hasVisualFeature([deep_purple_color]) and hasVisualFeature([petals_with_white_or_yellow_centers]) and hasVisualFeature([multiple_petals_with_floral_spikes]) and hasVisualFeature([delicate_petal_edges]);

    <!-- Class 14 (Iris) -->
    [Class_14] sqsubseteq hasVisualFeature([bright_yellow_color]) and hasVisualFeature([three_prominent_petals_with_flared_edges]) and hasVisualFeature([distinctive_veined_petals]) and hasVisualFeature([thick_textured_stamens_in_center]);
</tbox>

<abox>
    hasVisualFeature(Target, [bright_yellow_color]);
    hasVisualFeature(Target, [three_prominent_petals_with_flared_edges]);
    hasVisualFeature(Target, [distinctive_veined_petals]);
    hasVisualFeature(Target, [thick_textured_stamens_in_center]);
</abox>

<dl_explanation>
    The Target Image exhibits bright yellow petals, three prominent petals with flared edges, distinctive veining, and thick textured stamens in the center. These features directly satisfy the sufficient conditions for [Class_14] (Iris) as defined in the TBox. The absence of deep purple color, white/yellow centers, or floral spikes rules out [Class_81] (Clematis). Thus, the Target Image logically matches the necessary and sufficient conditions for the Iris class.
</dl_explanation>

